FBIS4-43867 "drweu120_g_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-120 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 CANADA Ouellet Announces 350 Troops To Be Sent to Rwanda Ouellet Announces 350 Troops To Be Sent to Rwanda LD2106205994 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 2030 21 Jun 94 LD2106205994 Montreal Radio Canada International English BFN [Text] Canada is sending 350 peacekeepers to Rwanda. The foreign affairs minister, Andre Ouellet, made the announcement in Ottawa today. The Canadians are communications specialists and they will be a part of the 4,000 member force the United Nations is putting together. Mr. Ouellet says the Canadians will leave for Rwanda within a few weeks. They'll join 11 other Canadian officers already serving with the UN contingent in Rwanda.
